    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">$-43.5B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model to estimate American Tower's intrinsic value, calculating the present value of future free cash flows.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Base Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>We begin with American Tower's reported FY2025 Free Cash Flow of <strong>$3.78 billion</strong>. As a REIT, FCF (or AFFO) is a key metric showing cash available for dividends and debt service.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>5-Year Growth Phase</h4>
      <p>We project cash flows growing at <strong>8% annually</strong> for the next five years. This balances steady demand for telecom infrastructure (5G densification, data usage growth) with the mature nature of their core markets.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Terminal Value</h4>
      <p>We calculate the terminal value using a <strong>2.5% perpetuity growth rate</strong>, reflecting long-term inflation and rent escalators built into their multi-year master lease agreements.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discounting</h4>
      <p>Future cash flows are discounted back to today at a <strong>9% discount rate (WACC)</strong>. This accounts for their steady business model but also acknowledges risks associated with their significant debt load and rising interest rates.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Equity Value per Share</h4>
      <p>We sum the present value of cash flows, add the net cash position (which is highly negative due to $44.9B in debt), and divide by 469 million diluted shares to arrive at the intrinsic value per share.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>Core Assumptions</h2>
  <p>A DCF valuation relies heavily on projected growth and risk assumptions.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Y1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">8%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        American Tower's revenue growth has been modest recently (5.1% in FY25), but FCF margins remain strong. An 8% growth rate assumes continued global data expansion and steady tenant leasing activity, balanced against potential churn or carrier consolidation.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">9%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        With the 10-Year US Treasury at 4.18%, a 9% discount rate provides a reasonable risk premium. While tower REITs have highly predictable cash flows (lowering equity risk), their reliance on debt financing makes them sensitive to interest rates.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">2.5%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        A 2.5% terminal rate aligns closely with long-term inflation targets. Tower leases typically include fixed annual escalators (often ~3% in the US or linked to local inflation internationally), supporting this baseline perpetual growth.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
          <th>FCF ($M)</th>
          <th>PV Factor</th>
          <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Base (FY2025)</td>
          <td>${fcf2025.toLocaleString()}</td>
          <td>—</td>
          <td>—</td>
        </tr>
        {projectedFCF.map(p => (
          <tr>
            <td>Year {p.year} ({2025 + p.year})</td>
            <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString()}</td>
            <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
            <td>${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE ═══ -->
  <h3>Terminal Value</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
          <th>Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Year 6 FCF (Year 5 × 1.025)</td>
          <td>${Math.round(fcfYear6).toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Terminal Value (FCF₆ ÷ (9% − 2.5%))</td>
          <td>${terminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FINAL CALCULATION ═══ -->
  <h3>Final Valuation</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
          <th>Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>PV of Phase 1 Cash Flows</td>
          <td>${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td>${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>= Enterprise Value</td>
          <td>${enterpriseValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>+ Net Cash (Cash − Debt)</td>
          <td>${netCash.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>= Equity Value</td>
          <td>${equityValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
